About Company:

Simtrum was founded in 2019 with the core mission to serve the optical industry with innovation and efficiency. Our founding team has decades of research and development experiences (across NUS and A-star) in high-end microscope systems. We now focus on confocal, super-resolution microscopy and other related fields, catering to both academia research and high end industrial production needs. Our proprietary high resolution microscopes adopt state of the art optical technology, image processing algorithms, with excellent imaging performance to meet the high resolution and fast imaging needs of our technology partners.
Simtrum is a young startup with many exciting opportunities to offer to the right candidates with the right mindset. We are now seeking the following commercial talents to join our team, to expand our reach and support our growth:
Job Descriptions:
1.provide quotations to customers and follow up on sales progress;
2.Update customer information and maintain the CRM system, and use the CRM system to develop and follow up with existing customers;
3. Responsible for communicating with product line suppliers to obtain product information and quotations;
4. Provide feedback and modification opinions to the marketing department on the company’s website and other marketing materials;
5. Prepare and organize and archive product information, contracts, payments, PO, DO, Invoice corresponding to customers and update the procurement system in a timely manner, etc.;
6. Responsible for logistics related matters.
Basic Requirements:
1.The ideal candidate is systematic, meticulous, and CAREFUL! High level of caution is required as you will be dealing with expensive and highly accurate optical instruments.
2.You also have to be highly organised to maintain our documentation and filing. While prior similar experiences are preferred, we are open for fresh graduates with the right attitude and willingness to learn to send in your application.
3.To do well in the Simtrum environment, you should be someone with initiative, curious, can-do attitude, flexible and eager to learn.
4.Fluency in both English and spoken Mandarin is a must, as you will be required to liaise with our Chinese counterparts.

1. Write articles, stories and assessment questions according to the needs of publication of company’s magazines (online and hardcopy) and books;
2. Editing manuscripts either on hard copy or on screen, to ensure consistency in style, punctuation and content;
3. Supporting in proofreading, copy-editing and amending documents; assisting the editorial team in sourcing for suitable materials and resources;
4. Provide support to subscription and school e-learning program.

